# AI Prompt Templates

Use these templates to keep agent responses consistent, reviewable, and easy to validate.

> **Canonical source: `AGENTS.md`** — this file provides ready-to-use prompt blocks.

---

## 1) Implementation Request Template

When asked to "implement", "fix", or "add feature":

```
Mode: [PRO/ULTRA/MAX] — [reason]

Task
- What the user wants (one sentence).

Research Done (mandatory before writing)
- Files read: [list]
- Patterns found: [existing similar implementations]
- Helpers to reuse: [from lib/]
- Cross-file deps: [grep results — list files importing changed modules]

Context
- Relevant files/paths.
- Existing behavior (brief).

Constraints
- Follow existing conventions (Next.js App Router, TS strict, RTL UI)
- Avoid breaking persisted schemas unless migration is included
- Persisted learner state must survive deploys (all `lib/*/storage.ts` domains); renaming content IDs (`dayId`, section/exercise ids) without a plan can orphan data — see `AGENTS.md` → Data & Storage Rules
- Never weaken configs to suppress errors
- Diff size: PRO ≤50 lines, ULTRA ≤300 lines, MAX no limit (each file needs rationale)

Acceptance Criteria
- (1) [Specific observable outcome]
- (2) [Specific observable outcome]
- (3) Quality gates pass for selected mode
- (4) No CRITICAL or HIGH issues in review
- (5) MCP Playwright visual check passes (if UI changed)
- (6) CI suite passes (ULTRA/MAX)

Quality Gates
- Follow quality-gates.mdc (mode-specific) + MCP Playwright + CI Final

Output Format
- Use handoff format from multi-agent-playbook.mdc
- Include verification report for ULTRA/MAX
```

---

## 2) Debugging / Investigation Template

When asked "why is it failing" or "what's wrong":

```
Mode: [PRO/ULTRA/MAX] — [reason]

Symptoms
- Error text, logs, and repro steps.

Hypotheses
- 1-3 plausible causes (based on code reading, not guessing).

What to Check
- Exact files/functions to inspect.
- Runtime assumptions (cookies, storage keys, routing gates).
- Cross-file impact: does this affect other modules?

Verification
- How you will confirm the fix (tests/commands/manual steps).
- If logic changed: npm run test:unit -- <specific-test-file>
- If routes/gates: npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/<specific>.spec.ts
```

---

## 3) Code Review Template

When asked to review:

```
Mode: [PRO/ULTRA/MAX] — [reason]

Security Gate
[ ] No hardcoded secrets (grep: API_KEY, SECRET, TOKEN, PASSWORD, sk-, pk_)
[ ] No console.log in production code
[ ] No sensitive data in data-testid values
[ ] User input validated at boundaries
[ ] Cookie operations safe
[ ] API route handlers validate inputs
[ ] No TODO/FIXME/HACK in security-critical code
Result: [PASS / FAIL — list findings]

Code Quality Check
[ ] TypeScript strict — no any, proper type guards
[ ] Functions focused and small
[ ] No deep nesting (>4 levels)
[ ] Error handling explicit, not swallowed
[ ] Follows existing conventions (@/* imports, naming, structure)
[ ] RTL preserved, dir="ltr" only for math inputs
[ ] data-testid on all interactive elements
[ ] Routes via lib/routes.ts (no hardcoded paths)
[ ] Storage schemas unchanged OR migration included
[ ] Backward compat: existing localStorage still loads; no orphan keys; content IDs not renamed without migration/content plan — see `AGENTS.md` → Data & Storage Rules

Review Output:
---
CODE REVIEW (kids_math)
========================
Mode:      [PRO/ULTRA/MAX]
Files:     [X files reviewed]

Issues Found:
[CRITICAL] file:line — description
[HIGH]     file:line — description
[MEDIUM]   file:line — description
[LOW]      file:line — description

Cross-File Impact:
- [X files import from changed modules]

What's Good:
- [specific positive observations]

Role Participation: [table — ULTRA/MAX only]

Verdict:   [APPROVE / CHANGES REQUESTED / BLOCK]
---

Verdict Rules:
- APPROVE: Zero CRITICAL, zero HIGH, security gate PASS
- CHANGES REQUESTED: HIGH issues found — must fix before merge
- BLOCK: CRITICAL issues found — no merge under any circumstances
```

