## 4) Plan Template

When asked to plan:

```
Mode: [PRO/ULTRA/MAX] — [reason]

Requirements Restatement
- What the user wants (1-3 sentences).

Risk Assessment
| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|------|----------|------------|
| Storage schema change | CRITICAL | Version bump + migration + MAX mode |
| RTL regression | HIGH | Manual RTL checklist + MCP Playwright |
| Cross-file impact >5 | HIGH | Explore phase first |

Files to Touch
- List every file, with reason.

Implementation Steps
1. [Step — concrete, testable, reversible]
2. ...

Multi-role Input (ULTRA/MAX)

**SeniorDev_TechLead:**
"Architecture: [concrete input]"

**SeniorFrontEnd_TechLead:**
"UI/RTL: [concrete input]"

**Dev_Architect:**
"Data flow: [concrete input]"

**QA_Architect:**
"Test strategy: [specific test files]"

**SeniorAutomation_Engineer:**
"Automation: [specific tests to add]"

Quality Gates
- PRO: lint + testids + targeted tests
- ULTRA: lint + testids + build + unit + targeted E2E + MCP Playwright + npm run test:qa
- MAX: npm run test:qa (full suite, no exceptions) + MCP Playwright (all screens)

MCP Playwright Plan
- Screens to visually verify: [list]
- Critical paths to test: [list]

Definition of Done
- [ ] [acceptance criterion 1]
- [ ] Quality gates pass for mode
- [ ] MCP Playwright visual check passes
- [ ] CI suite (npm run test:qa) passes
- [ ] Security gate PASS
- [ ] No CRITICAL or HIGH issues

> ⛔ CHECKPOINT: Plan Review
> Status: COMPLETE
> Awaiting your confirmation to proceed to Explore phase.
> Options: (proceed / revise / different approach / escalate mode)
```

